description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an Administrative Assistant at the Sussex Partnership, based in St Leonards-on-Sea, East Sussex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a busy service comprising a 23-bed Acute unit split into male and female wards and an 18-bed unit for older patients, alongside an Urgent Care service. You will work as part of a multi-disciplinary team to provide administrative support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Trust was recently upgraded by CQC as GOOD in every domain except CARING, which was EXCELLENT. Due to this we are now the third leading Mental Health Trust in the country. We will strive to maintain our standards and always improve where we can and you will play an important part in this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will be responsible for a wide range of duties to support managerial staff in both our in-patient and urgent care services, including arranging meetings, completing HR and other paperwork, taking notes, data collection, assisting with reports and other ad hoc duties as directed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must have excellent communication skills, the ability to manage competing demands and deadlines, great organisational skills and a desire to provide brilliant customer service. You must have a helpful and flexible attitude and a willingness to work as part of a busy team, as well as the ability to work alone. You must be able to use your initiative and be able to produce high quality materials and help manage office systems effectively and efficiently. You will deal with people at all levels internally and externally.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be enthusiastic, self-motivated, adaptable and able to work on your own initiative as well as part of a multidisciplinary team. Effective communication skills and a commitment to caring for patients must be demonstrated. You will require:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of software programmes / IT systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good organisational and time-management skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return we can offer:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comprehensive induction package&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supportive working environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent educational / training opportunities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job sharers will be considered&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Paul Richardson, Admin Team Leader on 0300 304 0253&lt;/p&gt;
